and no evil spirits or poltegeist visited you as george noory suggested or warned us about when playing with the ouija board?



--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, &quot;April Abercrombie&quot; &lt;april@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Exactly. And it may even be that it&#39;s both-sometimes it is us, but once in a while and actual entity comes through. But until I can really study it over a period time, I am just not convinced either way.
&gt; 
&gt;   ----- Original Message ----- 
&gt;   From: Zack Widup 
&gt;   To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com 
&gt;   Sent: Saturday, April 11, 2009 1:10 AM
&gt;   Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] An alternative to the usual ghost hunter stuff.
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt;   I tried an Ouija board once. My brother and I were given one by my grandmother, who found it in her attic. After asking many questions and getting all sorts of answers that ranged from gibberish to the totally absurd, I think we decided there was something in our joint subconsciouses that was making the planchette give the answers it did.
&gt; 
&gt;   That may not always be the case, though. I think if answers of some sort were given involving something that no one present would have the faintest idea about, and they turned out to be true or valid, then it might demonstrate spirit communication.
&gt; 
&gt;   Zack
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt;   On Fri, Apr 10, 2009 at 11:37 PM, April Abercrombie &lt;april@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt;     Well, if my husband would let me actually experiment with one, that would be the first step LOL!
&gt; 
&gt;     But what I would try and do is get some kind of verifiable information from the &quot;entity&quot; that I contact with the board to prove that it is communication from an actual, intelligent being and not just my own motor responses making he planchette move. It would have to be information that I have no knowledge of.
&gt; 
&gt;     If I could do that, and consistently, then I would be comfortable saying that I am actually talking to a spirit.
&gt; 
&gt;     The reason I have my doubts is that you have to be touching the planchette to get it to move. If it were an actual spirit, I would think that shouldn&#39;t be necessary. We all know ghosts can a do move objects.
&gt; 
&gt;     But this brings up another mystery - if the Ouija board is actual spirit communication, maybe there is a difference between the entities you can contact with it and your common ghost.
&gt; 
&gt;     April
